1
00:00:59,513 --> 00:01:00,946
German bandits at two o'clock!

2
00:01:01,114 --> 00:01:02,479
Increase throttle! Power dive!

3
00:01:08,288 --> 00:01:10,552
Spell it right, Rafe.

4
00:01:10,591 --> 00:01:14,083
"Rudder" is spelled with two Ds.

5
00:01:14,127 --> 00:01:16,095
Thanks, wingman.

6
00:01:17,331 --> 00:01:18,628
Whoa, bandits!

7
00:01:20,801 --> 00:01:22,068
Crack shootin', Danny.

8
00:01:22,135 --> 00:01:23,205
Crack shootin', Rafe.

9
00:01:23,303 --> 00:01:25,294
- Land of the free.
- Home of the brave.

10
00:01:44,691 --> 00:01:47,159
Great flyin', Dad!

11
00:01:49,262 --> 00:01:51,162
Come on.
I'm gonna teach you how to fly.

12
00:01:58,338 --> 00:02:01,034
- I get the front!
- No, you take the back.

13
00:02:01,074 --> 00:02:03,269
I'm bigger,
and I should be in front.

14
00:02:03,309 --> 00:02:05,573
I'm older,
and I'm teachin', so no.

15
00:02:05,612 --> 00:02:07,546
Wow.
It's like we're really flying.

16
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:10,447
Yeah, I did it lots of times.
Come on, you man the guns.

17
00:02:10,483 --> 00:02:11,916
I'll give her some throttle.

18
00:02:11,951 --> 00:02:13,942
We gotta get those
dirty German bandits.

19
00:02:18,925 --> 00:02:20,893
Oh, gosh!

20
00:02:26,866 --> 00:02:29,494
- Hang on!
- Make it stop, Rafe!

21
00:02:31,537 --> 00:02:33,164
I've seen my dad
do this lots of times.

22
00:02:33,206 --> 00:02:34,901
Don't worry!

23
00:02:39,846 --> 00:02:42,610
Oh, my gosh! We're flying!

24
00:02:42,649 --> 00:02:44,514
We're flying!

25
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:02,494
My dad's gonna kill me.

26
00:03:02,535 --> 00:03:05,163
Come on.

27
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:09,100
We flew!

28
00:03:09,142 --> 00:03:11,167
We flew! Yes!
I'm a pilot!

29
00:03:11,210 --> 00:03:12,871
- I know!
- Yeah!

30
00:03:14,981 --> 00:03:16,243
We flew.

31
00:03:16,282 --> 00:03:18,011
- You no-account boy!
- Daddy...

32
00:03:18,051 --> 00:03:19,780
I done told you,
you spend time playing...

33
00:03:19,819 --> 00:03:22,014
with this stupid boy
can't read...

34
00:03:22,055 --> 00:03:23,716
you ain't never goin'
to amount to nothin'!

35
00:03:23,756 --> 00:03:26,452
He ain't stupid, Daddy!

36
00:03:29,729 --> 00:03:31,128
Come on!

37
00:03:32,999 --> 00:03:35,832
Get on back home. Now!

38
00:03:38,438 --> 00:03:39,803
Get on up.

39
00:03:39,839 --> 00:03:41,534
You got work to do.

40
00:03:41,574 --> 00:03:44,202
Come on, get on home!

41
00:03:46,546 --> 00:03:48,571
You let him alone!

42
00:03:49,882 --> 00:03:51,713
Daddy, no!

43
00:03:51,751 --> 00:03:54,151
I will bust you open,
you dirty German!

44
00:03:54,187 --> 00:03:56,655
What'd you call me?

45
00:03:58,458 --> 00:04:01,552
I fought the Germans in France.

46
00:04:01,594 --> 00:04:05,587
And I fought 'em
in the trenches.

47
00:04:05,631 --> 00:04:07,792
And I pray to God
no one ever has to see...

48
00:04:07,834 --> 00:04:09,199
the things that I saw.

49
00:04:25,585 --> 00:04:28,179
You're my best friend.

50
00:04:29,922 --> 00:04:32,083
Daddy, wait!

51
00:04:42,468 --> 00:04:43,696
Adolf Hitler...

52
00:04:43,736 --> 00:04:45,761
builds the German
military machine...

53
00:04:45,805 --> 00:04:47,898
and drags all of Europe
into war.

54
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:50,306
But even while France
falls to Hitler...

55
00:04:50,343 --> 00:04:53,107
America still refuses
to join the fighting.

56
00:05:11,364 --> 00:05:13,457
- Where's McCawley and Walker?
- Still training, sir.

57
00:05:15,134 --> 00:05:17,261
All right, Danny.
Now let's show 'em how to fly.

58
00:05:17,303 --> 00:05:18,702
We're gonna play chicken.
You ready?

59
00:05:18,738 --> 00:05:21,070
This ain't the farm,
and these ain't no cropdusters.

60
00:05:21,107 --> 00:05:22,267
I'm not playing
chicken with you.

61
00:05:22,308 --> 00:05:23,798
Now don't be a baby.
I'll tell you what...

62
00:05:23,843 --> 00:05:26,243
- I'm not doing it, Rafe.
- I'm coming right at you.

63
00:05:26,279 --> 00:05:27,974
You can turn, or you can hit me.
It's up to you.

64
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:32,110
What the...

65
00:05:32,151 --> 00:05:33,345
Oh, boy.

66
00:05:36,622 --> 00:05:38,988
Why you always
bustin' my ass, Rafe?

67
00:05:39,025 --> 00:05:40,322
Which way you goin'?

68
00:05:42,228 --> 00:05:44,992
I guess I'll go right.
No, left. I'll go left.

69
00:05:47,333 --> 00:05:48,595
OK, we're goin' left, right?

70
00:05:48,634 --> 00:05:49,965
Right. Right?

71
00:05:50,002 --> 00:05:52,095
Right like we're goin' right,
or right like we're goin' left?

72
00:05:52,138 --> 00:05:53,696
Well, now you got me
all mixed up!

73
00:05:53,739 --> 00:05:55,764
I don't know.
Make up your mind.

74
00:05:58,077 --> 00:06:01,046
God, Rafe, we're going right!
Righty-tighty!

75
00:06:10,756 --> 00:06:12,781
Those are some smooth aces.

76
00:06:12,825 --> 00:06:14,952
Did you say something?

77
00:06:14,994 --> 00:06:17,224
'Cause let me tell ya,
those farm boys are grounded!

78
00:06:17,263 --> 00:06:19,561
Yes, sir, an entirely
unacceptable use...

79
00:06:19,599 --> 00:06:22,295
of m-military aircraft, sir.

80
00:06:23,703 --> 00:06:25,227
- Get my hat.
- Yes, sir.

81
00:06:25,271 --> 00:06:28,331
Get those hedge-hoppers
in Doolittle's office.

82
00:06:28,374 --> 00:06:30,740
After two years of training...

83
00:06:30,776 --> 00:06:33,142
you believe that
a $45,000 airplane...

84
00:06:33,179 --> 00:06:34,669
is there for your amusement?

85
00:06:34,714 --> 00:06:37,308
No, sir. I was just trying
to keep my edge, Major.

86
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:39,181
And when you did
the outside loop last week...

87
00:06:39,218 --> 00:06:41,686
what did you think that was?
Honing your skills?

88
00:06:41,721 --> 00:06:42,983
That's not training, McCawley.

89
00:06:43,022 --> 00:06:44,284
That's a stunt.

90
00:06:44,323 --> 00:06:46,587
And I personally
consider it to be reckless...

91
00:06:46,626 --> 00:06:50,118
and irresponsible.

92
00:06:50,162 --> 00:06:51,356
Major...

93
00:06:54,033 --> 00:06:55,330
How could that be,
when you're famous...

94
00:06:55,368 --> 00:06:57,097
for being the first man
in the world ever to do it?

95
00:06:57,136 --> 00:06:58,296
Don't get cute with me, son.

96
00:06:58,337 --> 00:07:00,805
No, sir, I don't mean
to be disrespectful.

97
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:03,638
I just think that...

98
00:07:03,676 --> 00:07:04,870
It is reckless
and irresponsible...

99
00:07:04,911 --> 00:07:06,173
if you're just doing it
to be a show-off.

100
00:07:06,212 --> 00:07:09,875
But I was doing it to try
to inspire the men, sir...

101
00:07:09,916 --> 00:07:11,247
in the way that
you've inspired me.

102
00:07:11,284 --> 00:07:13,411
I believe the French
even have a word for that...

103
00:07:13,452 --> 00:07:15,283
when the men get together
to honor their leaders.

104
00:07:15,321 --> 00:07:16,686
They call it an homage, sir.

105
00:07:16,722 --> 00:07:18,587
- A what?
- An homage, sir.

106
00:07:18,624 --> 00:07:20,285
That's bullshit, McCawley!

107
00:07:23,629 --> 00:07:26,689
But it's very,
very good bullshit.

108
00:07:26,732 --> 00:07:27,926
Thank you, sir.

109
00:07:30,736 --> 00:07:34,399
McCawley, you remind me
of myself fifteen years ago.

110
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:36,431
Which is why we need
to discuss this.

111
00:07:36,475 --> 00:07:38,466
Have a seat, son.

112
00:07:46,185 --> 00:07:49,018
The British have accepted you
into the Eagle Squadron.

113
00:07:49,055 --> 00:07:51,455
You're on your way
to England tomorrow...

114
00:07:51,490 --> 00:07:53,617
if you still want to go.

115
00:07:56,162 --> 00:07:58,130
Just a few British pilots
are all that stand...

116
00:07:58,164 --> 00:08:00,530
between Hitler
and total victory in Europe.

117
00:08:00,566 --> 00:08:02,591
They're gonna need
all the help they can get.

118
00:08:02,635 --> 00:08:04,102
Yes, sir. I'm on my way.

119
00:08:04,136 --> 00:08:06,502
Just for the record...

120
00:08:06,539 --> 00:08:08,439
I'm supposed to ask you
to reconsider.

121
00:08:08,474 --> 00:08:10,032
Sir?

122
00:08:10,076 --> 00:08:12,044
Sooner or later
we're gonna be in this war...

123
00:08:12,078 --> 00:08:14,069
whether we like it or not.

124
00:08:14,113 --> 00:08:16,445
And I'm gonna need
all of my best pilots.

125
00:08:16,482 --> 00:08:19,315
So it's my duty
to ask you to stay.

126
00:08:19,352 --> 00:08:22,515
Major, what would you do?

127
00:08:24,857 --> 00:08:26,586
If it was me...

128
00:08:28,861 --> 00:08:30,829
I'd go.

129
00:08:30,930 --> 00:08:33,330
Get out. Am I going bald
right back here?

130
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:37,799
Man, I am one good-lookin'
son of a bitch.

131
00:08:37,837 --> 00:08:39,464
Don't you ever die.

132
00:08:39,505 --> 00:08:42,133
Die. That's exactly...

133
00:08:42,174 --> 00:08:45,234
the concept
you gotta work tonight.

134
00:08:45,277 --> 00:08:48,713
You put a drop of this clove oil
under your eyes...

135
00:08:48,748 --> 00:08:50,773
and you let 'em sting
and well up.

136
00:08:50,816 --> 00:08:54,183
You get your nurse alone,
take a breath...

137
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:56,620
let her see your eyes glisten...

138
00:08:56,656 --> 00:09:01,093
and say, "Baby,
they're training me for war...

139
00:09:01,127 --> 00:09:04,028
"and I don't know
what'll happen...

140
00:09:04,063 --> 00:09:07,328
"but if I die tomorrow,
I want to know...

141
00:09:07,366 --> 00:09:11,393
"that we lived
all we could tonight."

142
00:09:11,437 --> 00:09:13,405
Come on, guys!
We got nurses waitin'.

143
00:09:13,439 --> 00:09:16,272
Come on, before the rest
of his hair falls out.

144
00:09:16,308 --> 00:09:19,766
How could you do this?

145
00:09:19,812 --> 00:09:21,336
Doolittle assigned me.

146
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:24,645
He wanted me to get
some real combat training in.

147
00:09:24,684 --> 00:09:25,844
Guess what?

148
00:09:25,885 --> 00:09:28,080
It's not training over there.
It's war.

149
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,384
Where the losers die,
and there aren't any winners...

150
00:09:30,423 --> 00:09:31,617
just guys who turn
into broken-down wrecks...

151
00:09:31,657 --> 00:09:32,817
like my father.

152
00:09:32,858 --> 00:09:34,086
I understand that, Danny.

153
00:09:34,126 --> 00:09:35,423
But I feel like
I got a duty to go.

154
00:09:35,461 --> 00:09:37,520
Don't preach to me
about duty, damn it.

155
00:09:37,563 --> 00:09:39,394
I wear the same uniform you do.

156
00:09:39,432 --> 00:09:42,265
Now, if trouble wants me,
I'm ready for it.

157
00:09:42,301 --> 00:09:43,461
But why go looking for it?

158
00:09:43,502 --> 00:09:45,629
God, Danny, come on.

159
00:09:45,671 --> 00:09:48,071
I'm gonna be twenty-five.
I might as well be an old man.

160
00:09:48,107 --> 00:09:50,166
They're gonna have me bein'
a flight instructor.

161
00:09:50,209 --> 00:09:52,643
I don't wanna teach loops
and barrel rolls.

162
00:09:52,678 --> 00:09:54,009
I wanna be a combat fighter.

163
00:09:54,046 --> 00:09:55,206
Hey, come on!

164
00:09:55,247 --> 00:09:58,410
The nurses can't
d-dance by themselves.

165
00:09:58,451 --> 00:10:00,214
Let's go.

166
00:10:09,261 --> 00:10:12,025
If the call of duty
means seeing 150 men...

167
00:10:12,064 --> 00:10:14,897
in their underwear every day,
we are here to serve.

168
00:10:16,135 --> 00:10:17,363
I can't believe it.

169
00:10:17,403 --> 00:10:19,428
Saturday night in New York City.

170
00:10:19,472 --> 00:10:21,133
Do you know what they're doing
where I come from?

171
00:10:21,173 --> 00:10:22,606
Nothing.

172
00:10:22,641 --> 00:10:24,438
Cow-tipping.

173
00:10:24,477 --> 00:10:25,705
Well, that's why
you joined the Navy, hon'.

174
00:10:25,745 --> 00:10:27,975
To get out of that dusty
little town and see the world.

175
00:10:28,013 --> 00:10:30,675
May I remind you, Barbara,
we're Navy nurses, not tourists.

176
00:10:30,716 --> 00:10:33,514
I joined to do
my patriotic duty and...

177
00:10:33,552 --> 00:10:35,747
to meet guys.

178
00:10:35,788 --> 00:10:37,221
Me, too.

179
00:10:37,256 --> 00:10:38,985
Girls, we're gonna have
so much fun tonight in the city.

180
00:10:39,024 --> 00:10:40,548
You've gotta tell them
the story, Evelyn.

181
00:10:40,593 --> 00:10:42,493
What?

182
00:10:42,528 --> 00:10:43,756
Oh, come on. Tell us.

183
00:10:43,796 --> 00:10:45,320
It's such a long story.

184
00:10:45,364 --> 00:10:47,332
We got time.

185
00:10:47,366 --> 00:10:49,231
I saw it happen.

186
00:10:49,268 --> 00:10:50,895
Well, it was
about four weeks ago...

187
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:53,629
What do you think is b-better?

188
00:10:53,672 --> 00:10:56,072
All in the one cheek,
or spreading them out?

189
00:10:58,544 --> 00:11:00,910
Fusco, Anthony.

190
00:11:05,651 --> 00:11:07,516
You all right, buddy?

191
00:11:07,553 --> 00:11:09,783
Sweetie, do you really
have to do this?

192
00:11:09,822 --> 00:11:12,882
I'm not gonna get yellow fever
in my barracks.

193
00:11:12,925 --> 00:11:15,917
No? If you'd rather,
she can do it.

194
00:11:20,466 --> 00:11:22,832
Whoa. Just gimme a minute.

195
00:11:22,868 --> 00:11:26,201
Honey, the government
says stick 'em, we stick 'em.

196
00:11:30,442 --> 00:11:31,875
Red, you all right?

197
00:11:34,313 --> 00:11:37,680
Eye exam number four?

198
00:11:37,716 --> 00:11:41,345
Listen, Doc, I have passed
a dozen medical checks.

199
00:11:41,387 --> 00:11:43,617
You write that,
they won't let me fly.

200
00:11:43,656 --> 00:11:46,124
Sorry, son.

201
00:11:46,158 --> 00:11:47,591
I'm gonna fail.

202
00:11:47,626 --> 00:11:49,253
They're gonna
take my wings away.

203
00:11:49,295 --> 00:11:51,559
No, they won't. Just relax.

204
00:11:51,597 --> 00:11:53,155
Read the bottom line, please.

205
00:11:53,199 --> 00:11:54,530
Just keep practicin'
the bottom line.

206
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,398
And don't worry.
I'm right behind you.

207
00:11:56,435 --> 00:11:59,233
J-L-M-K-P-O...

208
00:12:03,108 --> 00:12:04,700
Next.

209
00:12:04,743 --> 00:12:06,176
Ma'am.

210
00:12:09,215 --> 00:12:12,207
J-L-M-K-P-O-E-T-X.

211
00:12:12,251 --> 00:12:13,718
Eyes like an eagle, ma'am.

212
00:12:13,752 --> 00:12:15,652
Slow down, flyboy.

213
00:12:15,688 --> 00:12:18,418
And, instead of the bottom,
read the very top. Both eyes.

214
00:12:18,457 --> 00:12:21,585
Yeah.

215
00:12:21,627 --> 00:12:25,063
"C"...sorry, "J."

216
00:12:25,097 --> 00:12:27,065
"C"...

217
00:12:27,099 --> 00:12:28,361
- "W."
- "W."

218
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:30,664
- "Q."
- "Q."

219
00:12:30,703 --> 00:12:32,432
"Q."

220
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:37,201
Read the bottom line
again, please.

221
00:12:37,243 --> 00:12:41,270
But read it right to left
and every other letter.

222
00:12:47,987 --> 00:12:49,614
"E."

223
00:12:49,655 --> 00:12:52,249
"X."

224
00:12:52,291 --> 00:12:54,623
- X-E.
- X-E.

225
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:57,060
X-E, ma'am.

226
00:12:57,096 --> 00:12:59,724
Ma'am, I know how this looks.

227
00:12:59,765 --> 00:13:01,460
I'm sorry, Lieutenant,
I really am.

228
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,627
But Army and Navy
requires 20/20 vision.

229
00:13:03,669 --> 00:13:06,365
Oh, I... it's not a problem
with my eyes.

230
00:13:06,405 --> 00:13:07,633
I can see.

231
00:13:07,673 --> 00:13:09,470
I can hit a running rabbit
with a $3.00 pistol.

232
00:13:09,508 --> 00:13:11,066
I got a problem with letters,
that's all.

233
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:12,702
Well, maybe after
some schooling...

234
00:13:12,745 --> 00:13:14,372
you could come back
and take the test again.

235
00:13:14,413 --> 00:13:15,675
No, I had schooling.

236
00:13:15,714 --> 00:13:17,045
The teachers just never knew...

237
00:13:17,082 --> 00:13:19,050
what to make of it.
It's just letters.

238
00:13:19,084 --> 00:13:20,574
I mix 'em up sometimes.
That's all.

239
00:13:20,619 --> 00:13:23,952
I just get 'em
backward sometimes.

240
00:13:23,989 --> 00:13:27,425
Look here.
My math and spacial reasoning...

241
00:13:27,459 --> 00:13:28,858
and my verbal scores
are all excellent.

242
00:13:28,894 --> 00:13:30,725
But you barely passed
the written exam.

243
00:13:30,763 --> 00:13:32,924
Yeah, but he did pass it.
So, is it my turn now?

244
00:13:32,965 --> 00:13:36,298
- No, you'll wait your turn.
- Yes, ma'am.

245
00:13:36,335 --> 00:13:38,599
Ma'am, I'm never gonna
be an English teacher.

246
00:13:38,637 --> 00:13:41,128
But I know why I'm here.

247
00:13:41,173 --> 00:13:42,697
To be a pilot.

248
00:13:42,741 --> 00:13:44,402
And you don't dogfight
with manuals.

249
00:13:44,443 --> 00:13:46,434
You don't fly with gauges.

250
00:13:46,478 --> 00:13:47,775
I mean, it's all about
feeling and speed...

251
00:13:47,813 --> 00:13:49,178
and lettin' that plane
become like a part...

252
00:13:49,214 --> 00:13:50,806
of your body.
And that manual...

253
00:13:50,849 --> 00:13:53,147
says that a guy who's a slow
reader can't be a good pilot.

254
00:13:53,185 --> 00:13:55,244
That file says I'm
